The paper deals with image retrieval using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses aggregation methods and their performance, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on several benchmarks, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
